President Obama convened a National Security Council meeting to review the events in Boston, including the apprehension of Dzhokar Tsarnaev and the ongoing investigation. He was briefed by various officials, including the Attorney General, FBI Director, and Secretary of Homeland Security. The President commended the work done to pursue justice in the Boston Marathon bombing and stressed the importance of gathering intelligence to answer remaining questions about the attack. Vice-President Biden participated in the meeting via video-conference.